   "description":"Eric Gunnar Erici was a Colonel from Borås, born on June 16th, 1882 in Rinna, Östergötland. He was the son of Reverend Anton Erickson and Erika Erickson. Eric was married to Anna Östberg for 10 years and had four children: Jan, Lena, Maria-Ann, and Per-Olov. He had a studentexamen from Norrköping in 1900 and served in the military, becoming a Colonel in 1937 while serving in the Älvsborg Regiment. He was also a teacher at Karlberg War College and served on various boards and organizations throughout his life. Erici wrote Takt. ex. (25) and has been awarded the Order of Vasa (RSO), the Grand Silver Medal of the Order of the Sword (LandstMM), the Örebro Provincial Federation's Gold Medal (Örebro dfbSM), the I. Class of the Elfsborgs Province Federation Medal (Älvsb. IfbGM), and the Swedish Red Cross Merit Badge (FS ftjK)."
